  I have been experimenting with AE kiting lately (hadn't tried it much before since I'd been grouping a lot), and I'm getting pretty good at it. What I do, is I round up all the desired creatures, then try to root them all in the same general area (running back and forth), and then AE snare. As soon as I start hitting them, root usually breaks. Now I know all of you are thinking  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/01 1:43:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: On AE Kiting and Bonds of Force</span><hr size=1> skip the root step. get a sow and run around picking up a train of mobs. don't get too far away or you'll lose agro. once you get 4 run in a big cicle around the mobs 2 or 3 times. then run directly away from them for about 10 seconds. stop, turn around, and spam yout BoF button till  it goes off. nuke. nuke. nuke. you get the picture.<br>
<br>
BTW - best way to agro is with staff of temperate flux. if you don't have one, get one. until then just use a low delay weapon and run by poking at the mobs. <p><span style="font-size: 18px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Wizard of the 43rd Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br>
<i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showMessage?topicID=42.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showMessage?topicID=21.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.emailToFriend?topicID=38.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.threadControl?topicID=38.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=38.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=38.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm4">Rant Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm8">Mob Dropped Spells<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm10">Class Balance & Class Bugs<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm22">Out of Mana<option value="graffeswizardc